Awards
Laurence Olivier Award for Best New Musical


Groundhog Day is a musical comedy with music and lyrics by Tim Minchin, and a book by Danny Rubin. Based on the 1993 film of the same name written by Rubin and Harold Ramis, the musical made its world premiere try-out at The Old Vic in London in summer 2016 and opened at the August Wilson Theatre on Broadway on 17 April 2017. The plot centres around Phil Connors, an arrogant Pittsburgh TV weatherman[1] who, during an assignment covering the annual Groundhog Day event in Punxsutawney, Pennsylvania,[2] finds himself in a time loop, repeating the same day again and again.[3]



